olive oil
1 carrot
1 head broccoli
½ Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet udon noodles
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet curry powder
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs brown sugar
1 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 tbs soy sauce
1 packet Crushed Peanuts

• Boil the kettle.
• Thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Cut broccoli into small florets, then roughly chop stalk.
• Slice onion (see ingredients) into wedges. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook broccoli, carrot and onion, tossing, until tender, 6-8 minutes.
• Transfer to a plate.

• Meanwhile, half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Cook udon noodles over medium-high heat, gently stirring with a fork to separate, until tender, 1-2 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and set aside.

• Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and curry powder and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Return veggies to the pan, then add cooked noodles, oyster sauce, the brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce and cook, tossing occasionally, until combined, 1-2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

• Divide hawker-style pork and veggie udon noodles between bowls.
• Garnish with crushed peanuts to serve. Enjoy!